    <div class="ba-grid" id="tool-8" style="margin-top: 48px;">
      <div class="ba-col before" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">#8 · $99/MO · ENTERPRISE ONLY</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Hootsuite — Best for enterprise teams with social listening needs</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">The oldest name in social scheduling — and now priced exclusively for enterprise, at $99/month minimum with no free plan.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Hootsuite is overkill for anyone publishing under 50 posts per week. The Streams dashboard provides real-time monitoring across all connected accounts in customizable columns. Bulk scheduling via CSV handles high-volume publishing. 150+ app integrations connect to your CRM and analytics stack. For enterprise teams already embedded in a complex marketing tech stack, Hootsuite plugs in. For small businesses, $99/month for a tool that does what Buffer does for $18/month is hard to justify.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Social listening — real-time keyword and brand monitoring</h4><p>Streams dashboard shows mentions, competitor activity, and keyword alerts in customizable columns.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>150+ integrations — connects to your full enterprise tech stack</h4><p>Salesforce, Slack, HubSpot, and more. For teams with complex tool stacks, Hootsuite plugs in cleanly.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Bulk CSV scheduling — hundreds of posts uploaded in one file</h4><p>For high-volume publishing, CSV upload saves significant manual entry time.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: $99/month minimum with no free plan since 2023</h4><p>The price increase hit small businesses hardest. If you're not using social listening and enterprise integrations, you're overpaying by 3–5x compared to alternatives.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

