          <p class="ba-sub">500 posts per bulk upload and the lowest per-account cost of any agency-capable scheduler in 2026.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">SocialPilot wins the value-per-account calculation for agencies. The Professional plan at $25.50/month supports 10 social profiles. That's $2.55 per profile per month — the lowest per-account rate in this category. Bulk scheduling handles 500 posts in a single CSV upload. The white-label reporting lets you send branded PDFs to clients. It's not as polished as Sendible and the inbox isn't as powerful as Agorapulse, but for pure volume at low cost, SocialPilot delivers.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Lowest per-account cost — $2.55/profile on the base plan</h4><p>Compared to Buffer at $6/channel or Agorapulse at $79/user, SocialPilot is the cheapest way to manage multiple client accounts.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>500-post bulk upload — highest CSV limit in the category</h4><p>Upload an entire month of content in one CSV file. Ideal for agencies that batch-schedule content for clients.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>White-label PDF reports — client-facing branded reports included</h4><p>Send branded monthly reports to clients without paying for a separate reporting tool.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: interface and UX feel dated compared to newer tools</h4><p>SocialPilot hasn't had a major design refresh in several years. The functionality is there; the experience is rougher than Buffer or Later.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

