          <p class="ba-sub">The most expensive tool on this list — and the most powerful for brands where social media is a customer care channel.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">Sprout Social is a CRM that happens to schedule posts. The Smart Inbox unifies every DM, comment, mention, and review across all platforms into one stream. Team members can assign, tag, and resolve conversations. For brands handling hundreds of customer interactions daily, this eliminates platform-hopping. At $249/month for one user (5 social profiles), the pricing reflects the CRM depth, not the scheduling capability. If you're paying for Sprout Social primarily to schedule posts, you're overpaying by a factor of 10.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Smart Inbox — every message and mention, one unified stream</h4><p>The best-in-class social customer care tool. Every interaction, assignable to team members, with resolution tracking.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Social listening + sentiment analysis — keyword tracking at enterprise depth</h4><p>Competitor monitoring, trend identification, and sentiment scoring built into higher tiers.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✓</span><div><h4>Custom reporting — build dashboards for different stakeholders</h4><p>Executive summaries, platform-specific breakdowns, and campaign reports. Useful for agencies and enterprise marketing teams.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="ba-num">✗</span><div><h4>Honest con: $249/month per user is prohibitive for most businesses</h4><p>A 3-person team costs $747/month. For scheduling-only needs, that's 5–10x more expensive than every other option on this list.</p></div></li>
